dev.foxgirl.rembulan.util

Interface ByteIterator

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Iterator<Byte>

    public interface ByteIterator
extends Iterator<Byte>
    An iterator over a sequence of bytes.

    This class implements the Iterator interface. However, for performance reasons, it is preferable to use its nextByte() method directly in order to avoid result boxing.

    • Method Detail

      • nextByte

        byte nextByte()
        Returns the next byte from the sequence and increments the byte position.

        When there is no next byte to be read from the stream, this method throws a NoSuchElementException. Use Iterator.hasNext() to detect this condition.

        Returns:
        the next byte from the byte stream
        Throws:
        NoSuchElementException - if there are no more bytes in the stream
